<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-593-229  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 593 229.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  Dec 1990 v8 n12 p136(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bargain-basement LANs big and small. (Information Modes' LittleBig LAN and The $25 Network) (local area networks) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lauriston, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information Modes' Little Big LAN, $75 per LAN, allows users toshare drives, applications, printers and data files and runmulti-user LAN applications.andP;  Little Big LAN can link up to 254workstations over common Arcnet or Ethernet systems or 10microcomputers using parallel or serial cables or modems.andP;  Usersneed only one copy of Little Big LAN per network.andP;  The $25 Networklinks microcomputers by way of serial cables only.andP;  The product islimited only by the number of serial ports users can fit in a hubmicrocomputer.andP;  It does not tie up a user's microcomputer whilesomeone else uses its printer or files.andP;  The $25 Network, however,does not support DOS file locking which causes problems if twousers try to edit the same file.andP;  The $25 Network costs $25 forthe first LAN and $12.50 for each additional LAN at the samelocation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Information Modes (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Little Big LAN (Network operating system) (Product introduction)25$ Network (Utility program) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Network Operating SystemsUtility ProgramsProduct IntroductionSoftware PackagesLocal Area Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>